    {
      "id": "1ad721a36738f39dc1dfe039ca253cabdb249d8e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 549,
        "name": "Misc Code Checks Robot (Gatekeeper helper)",
        "username": "smatchreview",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2020-08-19 06:28:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCode-wise looks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b910458a87a9b40b7ad7722d1f970722815db7b4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-08-25 23:22:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nIt would be good to add a Test-Parameters line to run this with racer, to ensure that there are no leaks in the dcache/icache.\n\nIt would also make sense to add a test similar to sanity test_76() that is exercising the dcache/icache for *different* files and checking that the lustre_inode_cache slab is being cleaned up after the DLM locks are dropped from the client.\n\nAlso note that \"num_inodes()\" may not be working properly on newer kernels because the lustre_inode_cache slab is being merged into \"signal_cache\" on the client.  Either we need to mount the client with \"slab_nomerge\" mount option, or by changing that code to use /sys/kernel/slab/lustre_inode_cache/objects to get the number of slab objects.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "26c5343445731807947eff2dd12995318ce506e6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2020-08-26 01:44:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "60d1aa1761986929dc84f116862aec12aa2927b4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-08-26 20:15:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "652bbb16c4c3f2394f02ea1155ac580e268353c8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-08-27 03:26:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI've pushed patch https://review.whamcloud.com/39735 \"LU-13909 tests: get lustre_inode_cache count from sysfs\" to fix sanity test_76 so that it works properly on kernels with slab merge enabled.  If this patch is updated, it would be useful to either rebase on top of that one, and/or make an updated test_76b that verifies that the slab cache shrinks properly when the MDC DLM LRU is cleared.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "65c5b6b5de6bf8751805aae91542960d51183ba8",
      "author": {
